# Development Workflow

## Quick Reference

```bash
cargo build                             # Build library + examples
cargo test                              # Run all tests (no server required)
cargo run --example cli_demo            # Run CLI demo with Foundation data
cargo run --example cli_demo ./data.json ./schemas/  # Custom data
```

> **No `source env.sh` required.** The gcc-13 / RocksDB requirement was eliminated
> in Phase 2. Bundled SQLite compiles with any standard C compiler on PATH.

---

## First Time Setup

1. **Install prerequisites:**
   - Rust stable toolchain ‚Äî [rustup.rs](https://rustup.rs)
   - A C compiler (`gcc`, `clang`, or MSVC) ‚Äî needed only for `openssl-sys` (reqwest TLS)
   - *(Optional)* [Lemonade Server](https://github.com/lemonade-sdk/lemonade) for semantic embeddings

2. **Build:**
   ```bash
   cargo build       # ~30 seconds first time (bundled SQLite compilation, not RocksDB)
   ```

3. **Run tests:**
   ```bash
   cargo test        # All 52+ tests pass with no server required
   ```

4. **Run the CLI demo:**
   ```bash
   cargo run --example cli_demo
   ```

